rest_of_day_open: I think it'll go pretty well. I'm excited to get back to working full time in the lab next week, and I have plans that I'm looking forward to with my significant other. I think it will be challenging in that I'm starting new projects, but fulfilling as I'll be able to see people that I haven't seen for a while.
critical_positive: I was super happy with the person I was matched up with. She was kind, exuberant, and humble. Even though we had some technical issues in the beginning (only one of us could speak/hear the other at a time) we were able to work through it and still have a great conversation. It worked well that we weren't exactly the same (different age) but that we also had a lot in common (homeschool, being from a big family, faith, etc.).
critical_negative: One issue was that we couldn't hear each other without pressing a button to switch from one person to the other. This made it kind of awkward and we ended up having her always press it, so there were times when I wasn't sure when she could hear me, and other times where I wanted to say something but couldn't because the active mic was still on her side.

rest_of_day_open: I see it going well. I will celebrate my thirtieth anniversary with my husband. We will take a little trip; we will celebrate our dear friend's birthday and his surviving cancer one more year. I will do my usual cooking and taking care of my family. Hopefully we will go to a winery for a picnic as well.
critical_positive: I think right off the bat we found that we had homeschooling in common. I am a retired homeschool Mom and she a homeschool graduate. We also come from large families. I am the oldest of five and she the oldest of six. We found that we both enjoy literature and have a common faith background.
critical_negative: The only thing that didn't work well was the sound. Only one of us could speak at a time because with the microphone button only one could hear the other. But we just took turns talking and asking each other questions. It was really a very enjoyable conversation and I would welcome the opportunity to talk with her again.
